26:04.480 --> 26:05.682
- [Greg] See what?

26:05.682 --> 26:06.980
- [Darren] I mean, it was just a blur

26:06.980 --> 26:08.470
but it definitely looked like him.

26:08.470 --> 26:09.543
- [Greg] I can't see anything

26:09.543 --> 26:10.630
back there, man.
- It looked like

26:10.630 --> 26:12.920
Professor Zardonicus, Greg.

26:12.920 --> 26:14.010
- [Greg] What are you talking about?

26:14.010 --> 26:15.710
- I saw him go around that corner.

26:16.830 --> 26:17.663
- [Greg] Darren, you're not thinking

26:17.663 --> 26:18.496
about going back there?

26:18.496 --> 26:19.410
- Well yes, I'm thinking
about going back there.

26:19.410 --> 26:20.680
I just saw him!

26:20.680 --> 26:21.513
Plus, he's not gonna attack

26:21.513 --> 26:22.346
if there's two of us.
- Dude, look how sketchy

26:22.346 --> 26:23.611
that place is, man.

26:23.611 --> 26:24.460
What?

26:24.460 --> 26:26.690
- He won't attack if
there's two of us, Greg.

26:26.690 --> 26:28.350
- [Greg] Yeah, a guy with a gun might.

26:28.350 --> 26:30.600
So, maybe just call it a day.

26:30.600 --> 26:31.433
- Fine. Yeah.

26:31.433 --> 26:32.900
Let's call it a day, that'd be great,

26:32.900 --> 26:34.143
when we saw him just around the corner.

26:34.143 --> 26:35.118
I'm just...

26:35.118 --> 26:36.560
- [Greg] Darren?

26:36.560 --> 26:37.544
No fucking way.

26:37.544 --> 26:39.070
Darren!

26:39.070 --> 26:39.903
Darren!

26:40.770 --> 26:41.603
Fuck.

26:42.760 --> 26:43.593
Darren?

26:44.660 --> 26:45.940
Darren?

26:45.940 --> 26:46.773
Okay.

26:48.260 --> 26:49.630
Good.

26:49.630 --> 26:50.463
Calm down, calm down.

26:50.463 --> 26:52.079
He's gotta be here somewhere.

26:52.079 --> 26:53.218
Fuck.

26:53.218 --> 26:55.155
Just put the fucking switch on.

26:55.155 --> 26:56.317
- Hey.
- Darren, oh!

26:56.317 --> 26:57.467
- Did you see anything?

26:59.400 --> 27:00.400
- [Greg] What?

27:00.400 --> 27:01.563
- Did you see anything?

27:02.960 --> 27:03.880
- [Greg] No!

27:03.880 --> 27:05.400
- Shit.

27:05.400 --> 27:06.850
I didn't see anything either.

27:08.170 --> 27:09.749
It was definitely worth
a try though, right?

27:09.749 --> 27:11.430
(Darren chuckles)

27:11.430 --> 27:12.940
Right?

27:12.940 --> 27:14.130
- [Greg] Just...

27:14.130 --> 27:14.963
Can we go?

27:15.912 --> 27:17.665
- Well, yeah. I mean, sure.

27:17.665 --> 27:19.415
It's kinda creepy back here anyway.

27:22.539 --> 27:24.090
Are you coming or are you
just gonna stand there?

27:24.090 --> 27:24.923
- [Greg] Yeah, I'm coming.

27:24.923 --> 27:25.810
- Come on, let's go.

27:27.190 --> 27:28.470
Honestly, today was a little slow

27:28.470 --> 27:31.170
but tomorrow we're gonna
hit the ground running.

27:31.170 --> 27:34.240
The whole flyer thing, big waste of time.

27:34.240 --> 27:36.520
I say we go straight to the press.

27:36.520 --> 27:38.390
Go to the campus media outlets,

27:38.390 --> 27:39.694
see if we can't get some good--

27:39.694 --> 27:40.940
- Wait, Darren! I think I saw something!

27:40.940 --> 27:41.773
- What?

27:41.773 --> 27:44.190
- I don't know but I think
it went into the fountain.

27:44.190 --> 27:45.410
- The fountain, of course.

27:45.410 --> 27:46.736
That's the last place I'd think to look.

27:46.736 --> 27:47.710
- Exactly.
- Of course he'd go there.

27:47.710 --> 27:48.543
All right, come on.

27:48.543 --> 27:49.500
Start recording now.

27:49.500 --> 27:51.370
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Start recording, Greg!

27:51.370 --> 27:52.354
Come on!

27:52.354 --> 27:53.530
(soft music)

27:53.530 --> 27:54.363
- [Greg] Wait, wait.

27:54.363 --> 27:55.500
Sorry, I forgot my light.

27:55.500 --> 27:56.370
- You said he went in there?

27:56.370 --> 27:58.430
- [Greg] What? The fountain?

27:58.430 --> 27:59.600
Uh, yeah, yeah.

27:59.600 --> 28:02.490
- So Professor Zardonicus
might be aquatic.

28:02.490 --> 28:04.530
- [Greg] Uh, you know,
I'm not really too sure.

28:04.530 --> 28:05.993
- You know what? I am.

28:07.770 --> 28:08.770
- [Greg] Wait, Darren.

28:08.770 --> 28:10.541
You're not thinking of going in there.

28:10.541 --> 28:11.530
- No.

28:11.530 --> 28:13.100
I'm gonna lose Professor Zardonicus

28:13.100 --> 28:14.740
because I'm scared of a little water.

28:14.740 --> 28:15.990
What do you think, Greg?

28:15.990 --> 28:16.823
- [Greg] But wait, wait.

28:16.823 --> 28:17.656
We can't do that.

28:17.656 --> 28:18.748
No, no, wait, Darren, Darren!

28:18.748 --> 28:20.116
No, come back here. Darren!

28:20.116 --> 28:23.199
(tense guitar music)

28:52.590 --> 28:53.860
- So, I mean, at least tonight

28:53.860 --> 28:55.200
wasn't a complete waste, right?

28:55.200 --> 28:56.400
- [Greg] No, not at all.

28:56.400 --> 29:00.204
- Now we know Professor
Zardonicus is at least buoyant!

29:00.204 --> 29:02.785
- [Greg] He's extremely buoyant!

29:02.785 --> 29:03.618
- [Security] Come back here!

29:03.618 --> 29:04.451
- Oh shit!

29:04.451 --> 29:05.290
See?

29:05.290 --> 29:08.100
The campus doesn't wanna know the truth.

29:08.100 --> 29:08.933
Fuck you!

29:08.933 --> 29:10.660
(Greg laughs)

29:10.660 --> 29:12.142
- [Rachel] Wait, you made him do what?

29:12.142 --> 29:13.910
- Oh, I had to.

29:13.910 --> 29:15.140
I had to call his bluff, man,

29:15.140 --> 29:16.770
and he did it.

29:16.770 --> 29:18.040
- [Rachel] Wait, Greg,
you could've been caught,

29:18.040 --> 29:18.873
both of you.

29:18.873 --> 29:19.854
- Ah, but we weren't.

29:19.854 --> 29:21.450
- [Rachel] That's not...

29:21.450 --> 29:22.283
Whatever.

29:22.283 --> 29:23.170
- Fuck, this is cool.

29:23.170 --> 29:24.003
- [Rachel] Okay, wait.

29:24.003 --> 29:26.710
I'm having a really hard
time focusing on your face.

29:26.710 --> 29:28.589
- Well, just press the button.

29:28.589 --> 29:29.895
- [Rachel] Okay, yeah.

29:29.895 --> 29:31.047
- No, that button right there.

29:31.047 --> 29:31.880
No that's--

29:31.880 --> 29:34.480
- [Rachel] So, what's
the course of action?

29:34.480 --> 29:35.313
Like?

29:36.393 --> 29:39.043
Do you think he's dangerous?
- And he's in my movie.

29:40.455 --> 29:41.781
What'd you say?

29:41.781 --> 29:43.440
- [Rachel] I said do you
think he's dangerous?

29:43.440 --> 29:44.273
- Well, no.

29:44.273 --> 29:45.720
He's like...

29:45.720 --> 29:46.740
He's a littler pretentious

29:46.740 --> 29:48.393
but he's not gonna hurt anybody.

29:49.487 --> 29:52.187
- [Rachel] How long do you
think you can keep this up?

29:53.320 --> 29:55.210
- As long as he wants to.

29:55.210 --> 29:58.420
Could I get him to go on like public news?

29:58.420 --> 30:01.040
Could we set something
up like we're gonna--

30:01.040 --> 30:02.156
- [Rachel] Come back down to earth.

30:02.156 --> 30:03.130
Come over here. Sit down.

30:03.130 --> 30:04.396
- Why? It's cool.

30:04.396 --> 30:08.280
- [Rachel] Okay, real question, Greg.

30:08.280 --> 30:10.823
Do you actually know what you're doing?

30:14.130 --> 30:15.313
- Yeah, I'd say so.

30:16.760 --> 30:18.630
After confirming Darren's sincerity

30:18.630 --> 30:20.490
with the fountain incident,

30:20.490 --> 30:21.900
I began to wonder

30:21.900 --> 30:24.490
could he persuade people to his beliefs

30:24.490 --> 30:26.330
on conviction alone?

30:26.330 --> 30:28.000
Stranger things have happened

30:28.000 --> 30:29.850
and stranger beliefs have spread.

30:29.850 --> 30:32.280
Could Darren be sitting
on a potential cult

30:32.280 --> 30:33.850
akin to Heaven's Gate?

30:33.850 --> 30:35.740
However, our second day of activities

30:35.740 --> 30:37.350
proved that Darren's beliefs

30:37.350 --> 30:39.653
were not so contagious.

30:40.510 --> 30:41.343
- Let me tell you!

30:41.343 --> 30:43.363
Do not be afraid of those who can kill

30:43.363 --> 30:45.280
both the body and the soul!

30:45.280 --> 30:47.685
Matthew 10:28.

30:47.685 --> 30:50.580
Do not be afraid of those
who can kill the body

30:50.580 --> 30:52.704
but cannot kill the soul.
- Jesus.

30:52.704 --> 30:54.380
- [Greg] Literally.

30:54.380 --> 30:57.180
- [Darren] I mean, you have to
admire his tenacity, really.

30:57.180 --> 30:59.810
- [Greg] I don't know if I'd
call it tenacity, Darren.

30:59.810 --> 31:01.750
- He's out here defending his beliefs,

31:01.750 --> 31:03.638
no matter how controversial.

31:03.638 --> 31:04.800
What would you call it?

31:04.800 --> 31:07.840
I mean, he really reminds
me a little bit of...

31:07.840 --> 31:09.108
Wait.
- What?

31:09.108 --> 31:10.040
- Wait, wait.

31:10.040 --> 31:10.873
Follow my lead.

31:10.873 --> 31:11.706
- [Greg] Wait, Darren, no.

31:11.706 --> 31:12.830
Come on, don't do this.

31:12.830 --> 31:14.440
- Do you believe what I'm saying?

31:14.440 --> 31:16.600
Do you--
- Hold on. Hi.

31:16.600 --> 31:17.780
How's it going?

31:17.780 --> 31:18.613
- What is this?

31:18.613 --> 31:20.370
Are you trying to humiliate
me for my beliefs?

31:20.370 --> 31:21.203
- Well, no.

31:21.203 --> 31:22.170
No, no, no. Not at all.

31:22.170 --> 31:23.610
I respect what you're doing out here,

31:23.610 --> 31:25.140
standing up for your beliefs like that.

31:25.140 --> 31:26.700
- Don't patronize me.

31:26.700 --> 31:27.533
- No, no, no.

31:27.533 --> 31:28.500
I would not patronize you.

31:28.500 --> 31:29.683
I'm a fellow believer.

31:30.550 --> 31:32.060
- You're a fellow believer?

31:32.060 --> 31:33.913
- Well, yes. I do believe.

31:34.960 --> 31:36.600
- A college student

31:36.600 --> 31:38.459
who isn't a radical atheist.

31:38.459 --> 31:40.330
(laughs) All the proof of God that I need.

31:40.330 --> 31:42.435
(Darren laughs)

31:42.435 --> 31:43.780
(Darren clears throat)

31:43.780 --> 31:45.520
So what's with the camera?

31:45.520 --> 31:48.670
- Well, actually I was gonna get to that.

31:48.670 --> 31:49.503
I actually came over here

31:49.503 --> 31:50.973
to give you one of these.

31:54.000 --> 31:55.610
- I'm confused.

31:55.610 --> 31:57.120
Is this...

31:57.120 --> 31:58.650
Did your little brother draw this?

31:58.650 --> 31:59.741
- Well, no, that is...

31:59.741 --> 32:02.320
That's Professor Zardonicus, see?

32:02.320 --> 32:03.400
- Professor what?

32:03.400 --> 32:04.270
- Zardonicus.

32:04.270 --> 32:06.590
I think it might be a Hungarian name.

32:06.590 --> 32:08.060
My friend and I are actually out here

32:08.060 --> 32:09.400
trying to prove his existence.

32:09.400 --> 32:10.860
I was just wondering if you could,

32:10.860 --> 32:12.000
I don't know, keep an eye out,

32:12.000 --> 32:13.430
let us know if you see him.

32:13.430 --> 32:15.590
- I mean, this looks like a monster.

32:15.590 --> 32:16.930
- Well, he is.

32:16.930 --> 32:19.470
Not to put too fine a
point on it or anything,

32:19.470 --> 32:20.980
maybe a creature.

32:20.980 --> 32:22.577
Whatever the more
politically correct term is.

32:22.577 --> 32:23.760
- Wait, wait, wait, wait.

32:23.760 --> 32:25.410
You're trying to get me to believe

32:25.410 --> 32:26.710
in a damn monster?

32:26.710 --> 32:27.543
- Well, yeah.

32:27.543 --> 32:29.170
You're a believe, so believe.

32:29.170 --> 32:31.160
- I believe in the Lord!

32:31.160 --> 32:31.993
- Okay.

32:31.993 --> 32:32.900
So do I.

32:32.900 --> 32:33.733
Congratulations!

32:33.733 --> 32:35.440
I've scratched your
back. Now scratch mine.

32:35.440 --> 32:36.990
I think that's what
Christ would've wanted.

32:36.990 --> 32:38.580
- I'm not gonna support this insanity!

32:38.580 --> 32:40.292
Do I look like a lunatic to you?

32:40.292 --> 32:43.180
- No, you look like an
open-minded individual

32:43.180 --> 32:44.483
which is why I approached you

32:44.483 --> 32:45.316
in the first place.
- Will you just

32:45.316 --> 32:46.530
leave me alone?

32:46.530 --> 32:47.730
Just go!
- Why?

32:47.730 --> 32:48.563
- Go!

32:48.563 --> 32:49.800
Just leave me alone!
- You don't believe!

32:49.800 --> 32:51.132
- Darren, let's go.

32:51.132 --> 32:52.030
Let's go, let's go, let's go.

32:52.030 --> 32:53.470
- You believe in nothing.

32:53.470 --> 32:56.420
- [Greg] So, Darren, what
do you think went wrong?

32:56.420 --> 32:58.310
- Um, I don't know.

32:58.310 --> 33:00.550
It seemed like all the cards

33:00.550 --> 33:02.350
were stacked in our favor, you know?

33:03.610 --> 33:05.510
I approached a like-minded individual

33:05.510 --> 33:08.193
and I guess he didn't believe me.

33:09.716 --> 33:12.970
I thought he might relate
to what I was going through

33:12.970 --> 33:16.480
but even if he doesn't believe me,

33:16.480 --> 33:17.840
then who the hell will?

33:17.840 --> 33:19.250
- [Greg] Darren, you don't wanna relate

33:19.250 --> 33:20.270
to guys like him, right?

33:20.270 --> 33:22.743
I mean, nobody takes him seriously.

33:23.780 --> 33:26.077
- Greg, there's an old saying

33:26.077 --> 33:28.823
that goes beggars can't be choosers.

33:30.300 --> 33:32.550
You know who the beggar
is in this situation?

33:33.700 --> 33:35.313
'Cause it sure as hell isn't him.

33:41.700 --> 33:42.950
- [Greg] Hey, Darren,

33:42.950 --> 33:45.600
do you think it might be your approach?

33:45.600 --> 33:48.120
- Do I think what might be my approach?

33:48.120 --> 33:51.023
- [Greg] Why people might
not be resonating with you?

33:52.040 --> 33:54.200
- This is just how I am, Greg.

33:54.200 --> 33:55.040
- [Greg] Well, think of it this way.

33:55.040 --> 33:57.010
So you have regular Christians

33:57.010 --> 34:00.110
and then you have fundamentalist
Christians like that guy.

34:00.110 --> 34:02.520
Now, even though these people

34:02.520 --> 34:04.840
basically believe the same kinda stuff,

34:04.840 --> 34:06.940
one is accepted by society

34:06.940 --> 34:08.530
and the other isn't.

34:08.530 --> 34:10.706
So why do you think that is?

34:10.706 --> 34:12.450
- I mean, it could have something to do

34:12.450 --> 34:14.250
with the whole your mom's a whore

34:14.250 --> 34:15.860
and the church knows it signs.

34:15.860 --> 34:17.250
- [Greg] Well, the signs are indicative

34:17.250 --> 34:18.770
of a bigger problem though, right?

34:18.770 --> 34:20.090
They're too blunt.

34:20.090 --> 34:21.923
And I think you're kinda too blunt.

34:23.590 --> 34:24.583
- I'm too blunt?

34:25.810 --> 34:27.040
- [Greg] Well...

34:27.040 --> 34:29.400
So the priests that I had growing up,

34:29.400 --> 34:31.350
they had a certain way
of talking about things.

34:31.350 --> 34:33.200
Like they eased you into it.

34:33.200 --> 34:34.540
They didn't beat you over the head

34:34.540 --> 34:37.400
with this apocalyptic stuff.

34:37.400 --> 34:38.233
- Okay.

34:38.233 --> 34:41.120
So, I mean, what do I do?

34:41.120 --> 34:42.690
- [Greg] Well, you know,

34:42.690 --> 34:44.833
we could try a PR touch up.

34:45.990 --> 34:48.660
- But I wouldn't even know where to begin.

34:48.660 --> 34:49.493
- I would.

34:50.940 --> 34:52.270
While this wouldn't get us any closer

34:52.270 --> 34:54.380
to proving the existence
of Darren's monster,

34:54.380 --> 34:56.070
my curiosity compelled me

34:56.070 --> 34:59.470
to suggest something rather unorthodox

34:59.470 --> 35:02.005
which he thankfully accepted.

35:02.005 --> 35:04.320
- First, just let me say thank you so much

35:04.320 --> 35:05.610
for meeting with me, Father.

35:05.610 --> 35:06.443
- Absolutely.

35:06.443 --> 35:08.120
I'm always happy to talk.

35:08.120 --> 35:11.280
Especially when it's about
something urgent, as you put it.

35:11.280 --> 35:14.020
- Yes, I would say it's urgent.

35:14.020 --> 35:16.920
I was actually hoping to get some advice.

35:16.920 --> 35:19.980
- You know, it's not often
that someone your age

35:19.980 --> 35:22.200
comes to me for spiritual advice.

35:22.200 --> 35:23.670
It's...

35:23.670 --> 35:25.920
Honestly, it's quite touching for me.

35:25.920 --> 35:29.100
- Well, you know, it is spiritual

35:29.100 --> 35:31.810
but at the same time it isn't.

35:31.810 --> 35:33.640
You know what I mean?

35:33.640 --> 35:36.660
- No, I'm sorry. I don't follow.

35:36.660 --> 35:37.713
- Let me rephrase.

35:39.060 --> 35:42.740
I'm actually thinking of
becoming an ordained minister.

35:42.740 --> 35:44.270
- Oh.

35:44.270 --> 35:45.290
Well, that's wonderful.

35:45.290 --> 35:48.050
- Yeah, but I was hoping you could help me

35:48.050 --> 35:51.560
with the approach to the more
personable side of priesthood.

35:51.560 --> 35:52.393
- Personable?

35:53.600 --> 35:56.140
- Well, maybe I phrased it weird.

35:56.140 --> 35:57.770
What I meant was,

35:57.770 --> 36:00.040
when I preach the word,

36:00.040 --> 36:02.630
I'm met with scorn and mockery.

36:02.630 --> 36:04.290
- Oh, speak no more.

36:04.290 --> 36:07.480
Everybody in the church
is in the exact same boat.

36:07.480 --> 36:08.840
- Well, yeah, that's the thing though.

36:08.840 --> 36:10.770
You guys have a boat.

36:10.770 --> 36:12.840
I'm kind of floundering at sea here.

36:12.840 --> 36:16.533
I mean, how do you get your
word to resonate with people?

36:18.250 --> 36:21.243
- Well, that's a difficult
question because--

36:21.243 --> 36:22.670
- Oh, just a second.

36:22.670 --> 36:23.720
I brought a notebook.

36:25.204 --> 36:27.400
I'm gonna take some notes, you know.

36:27.400 --> 36:31.510
- Faith means different
things to different people.

36:31.510 --> 36:34.950
But I think it's also
important to keep in mind

36:34.950 --> 36:37.880
that you're asking people to take a leap

36:38.760 --> 36:41.230
and people don't leap out of fear.

36:41.230 --> 36:42.763
It only paralyzes them.

36:44.470 --> 36:46.560
It has to be for love.

36:46.560 --> 36:50.320
And you have to make people understand

36:50.320 --> 36:52.730
or to guide them to the understanding

36:52.730 --> 36:57.550
that to worship God and to accept Him,

36:57.550 --> 36:59.410
is to be loved.

36:59.410 --> 37:00.960
- That's amazing.

37:00.960 --> 37:02.960
That, really, that's fantastic.

37:02.960 --> 37:04.220
- Thank you.

37:04.220 --> 37:05.960
But it's also important to keep in mind

37:05.960 --> 37:07.690
that it's not just about faith--

37:07.690 --> 37:09.610
- How do you make people believe

37:09.610 --> 37:12.040
in the whole resurrection thing?

37:12.040 --> 37:14.340
That seems like kind of
a big pill to swallow.

37:16.440 --> 37:19.483
- Um. (stutters)

37:20.760 --> 37:22.680
- Wow. They really knew their stuff, huh?

37:22.680 --> 37:24.130
- What'd I tell you?

37:24.130 --> 37:26.160
- Look, I don't know what
to do with this information,

37:26.160 --> 37:27.740
but when I find out it's gonna be like,

37:27.740 --> 37:30.220
look out Professor, here I come!

37:30.220 --> 37:31.680
- Well, just follow the model, right?

37:31.680 --> 37:35.090
- Yeah but, I mean, where
am I gonna find my crowd?

37:35.090 --> 37:36.390
- [Greg] Wherever you can.

37:37.400 --> 37:41.261
The resulting solution was drastic

37:41.261 --> 37:42.883
to say the least.

37:43.720 --> 37:46.410
- That it does not cast their sunlight

37:46.410 --> 37:48.023
in the Garden of Eden.

37:49.859 --> 37:51.120
- [Greg] You nervous, Darren?

37:51.120 --> 37:52.380
- What?

37:52.380 --> 37:54.000
- [Greg] Just asking if you're nervous.

37:54.000 --> 37:57.310
- I mean, a little bit but, you know,

37:57.310 --> 37:59.800
I did theater in high school, so.

37:59.800 --> 38:00.633
- [Greg] Like what?

38:00.633 --> 38:03.201
- You know, "King Lear",
"Hamlet", "Macbeth", all the--

38:03.201 --> 38:04.034
- Shh!

38:06.690 --> 38:08.190
- What the fuck?

38:08.190 --> 38:09.980
- [Greg] You're not supposed to say

38:09.980 --> 38:11.367
the name of the play.

38:11.367 --> 38:12.390
- Superstitious much?

38:12.390 --> 38:13.223
All I said was "Macbeth".

38:13.223 --> 38:15.720
- [Greg] But there's a
curse around "Macbeth".

38:15.720 --> 38:16.553
That's the idea.

38:16.553 --> 38:17.960
That's why people get upset.

38:17.960 --> 38:19.478
- So, what? I shouldn't
say "Macbeth" anymore?

38:19.478 --> 38:20.395
- No.
- Shh!

38:21.416 --> 38:22.698
- Fine, I'll stop saying "Macbeth".

38:22.698 --> 38:23.740
Is that what you want?

38:23.740 --> 38:25.340
- [Greg] Just say the
Scottish play instead.

38:25.340 --> 38:26.371
- What?

38:26.371 --> 38:27.204
- [Greg] The Scottish play.

38:27.204 --> 38:28.680
Say that instead.
- I'm talking about "Macbeth".

38:28.680 --> 38:29.920
I'm not talking about a Scottish play.

38:29.920 --> 38:31.000
What are you talking about?

38:31.000 --> 38:35.890
- I say hate is the
ancient theme run afoul

38:35.890 --> 38:37.533
in mankind's passage.

38:38.510 --> 38:43.163
- [Greg] Darren, I'm having
second thoughts about this.

38:44.170 --> 38:45.500
- I'm the one that's
going out there on stage.

38:45.500 --> 38:46.749
You're just filming it.

38:46.749 --> 38:48.585
- [Greg] Yeah, I just...

38:48.585 --> 38:51.780
It seemed like an
interesting idea at the time

38:51.780 --> 38:54.990
but being here, I don't know
how you're gonna come across.

38:54.990 --> 38:56.791
- Come across?

38:56.791 --> 38:58.663
This audience right here?

38:59.940 --> 39:02.470
They're built around acceptance

39:02.470 --> 39:04.463
and never ending love.

39:05.340 --> 39:06.870
They want the truth to come out, right?

39:06.870 --> 39:07.830
I mean, that's what they're--

39:07.830 --> 39:08.820
- [Greg] When they're saying coming out

39:08.820 --> 39:10.180
they're talking about something different.

39:10.180 --> 39:11.013
- Listen, Greg.

39:11.013 --> 39:12.330
I think you're over analyzing this.

39:12.330 --> 39:14.697
These people are very
accepting, all right?

39:14.697 --> 39:17.670
They embrace everyone with open arms.

39:17.670 --> 39:19.430
They're gonna embrace a creature

39:19.430 --> 39:21.380
who's been locked away by society,

39:21.380 --> 39:23.190
who's been put in a corner,

39:23.190 --> 39:25.880
who's been seen as a monster.

39:25.880 --> 39:29.107
- Yet you force me to look away from you.

39:30.324 --> 39:32.277
(audience applauding)

39:32.277 --> 39:35.527
(Darren clears throat)

39:43.380 --> 39:45.300
- Hi, everyone.

39:45.300 --> 39:46.890
Thank you so much for coming out.

39:46.890 --> 39:49.260
My name is Darren.

39:49.260 --> 39:52.890
And I wanna share something
with you guys tonight.

39:52.890 --> 39:55.160
You see, because there's someone

39:55.160 --> 39:56.970
very near and dear to my heart

39:56.970 --> 39:59.190
that needs to come out to the world,

39:59.190 --> 40:02.644
that needs accepting people such as you.

40:02.644 --> 40:07.644
And of course, I'm talking
about Professor Zardonicus.

40:07.870 --> 40:09.100
Yes, that's right.

40:09.100 --> 40:11.090
Professor Zardonicus.

40:11.090 --> 40:16.090
The secret of this university
for the past 50 years.

40:16.160 --> 40:17.880
He has been the subject

40:17.880 --> 40:22.880
of cynicism and skepticism,
mockery, and scorn,

40:24.130 --> 40:26.180
because we've been misunderstanding him.

40:26.180 --> 40:28.160
Oh, we've been all wrong.

40:28.160 --> 40:30.120
You see, because Professor Zardonicus

40:30.120 --> 40:33.470
is not a creature who's driven by fear.

40:33.470 --> 40:36.460
But instead, driven by love.

40:36.460 --> 40:39.360
He needs us to find him

40:39.360 --> 40:42.180
because only by finding
Professor Zardonicus

40:42.180 --> 40:44.630
can we truly find ourselves.

40:44.630 --> 40:46.170
I'm here today to tell you

40:46.170 --> 40:49.670
that Professor Zardonicus has
only remained in the shadows

40:49.670 --> 40:52.270
because we have not made a space for him

40:52.270 --> 40:55.340
in our heart and souls.

40:55.340 --> 40:57.952
For the begotten are not the beloved.

40:57.952 --> 40:59.860
- Shut up!
- Because the beloved

40:59.860 --> 41:01.360
are those who believe

41:01.360 --> 41:03.108
in Professor Zardonicus.
- Boo!

41:03.108 --> 41:04.870
(audience jeering)
- Would you stop?

41:04.870 --> 41:06.210
I'm not done!

41:06.210 --> 41:07.453
I'm not done yet!

41:08.361 --> 41:09.680
I'm not done yet!

41:09.680 --> 41:11.186
I wasn't done!

41:11.186 --> 41:13.417
You're supposed to be accepting people!

41:13.417 --> 41:14.796
I wasn't done yet!

41:14.796 --> 41:16.530
I wasn't done yet.

41:16.530 --> 41:18.540
See, Greg? That's what happens!

41:18.540 --> 41:20.647
That's what happens when you
try to put yourself out there

41:20.647 --> 41:22.450
and get people to believe in something

41:22.450 --> 41:23.790
that hasn't been fucking programmed

41:23.790 --> 41:24.874
into their minds since birth!

41:24.874 --> 41:25.917
- [Greg] Darren, it's okay.

41:25.917 --> 41:27.750
- No, it's not okay, Greg!

41:27.750 --> 41:28.583
It's not okay!

41:28.583 --> 41:29.770
They kicked me off the stage.

41:29.770 --> 41:31.310
I had five fucking pages left

41:31.310 --> 41:32.330
and they kicked me off the stage

41:32.330 --> 41:33.620
like my opinion didn't matter!

41:33.620 --> 41:36.100
- [Greg] Maybe that's
because an LGBT poetry slam

41:36.100 --> 41:37.110
isn't the best platform--

41:37.110 --> 41:38.910
- That was your idea, Greg!

41:38.910 --> 41:40.470
That was your fucking idea!

41:40.470 --> 41:42.315
- [Greg] It was a joke.

41:42.315 --> 41:43.396
It was a joke!

41:43.396 --> 41:46.146
(Darren sobbing)

41:55.327 --> 41:57.177
- [Darren] I just don't get it, Greg.

41:58.718 --> 42:00.223
- [Greg] You don't get what?

42:08.166 --> 42:10.257
- Has it ever occurred to you

42:10.257 --> 42:12.836
that the right place and time

42:12.836 --> 42:15.586
is the only difference between
a mad man and a prophet?

42:19.820 --> 42:21.473
- [Greg] I don't know about that.

42:27.110 --> 42:29.060
- Professor Zardonicus deserves better.

42:32.990 --> 42:35.240
He deserves better than
these fucking people.

42:38.310 --> 42:39.143
- Okay.

42:43.520 --> 42:46.810
Upset as he was about
the poetry night debacle,

42:46.810 --> 42:48.480
Darren found that the event had in fact

42:48.480 --> 42:50.350
succeeded in raising his profile.

42:50.350 --> 42:51.500
So he was invited...

42:52.730 --> 42:55.590
Um, kinda doing something.

42:55.590 --> 42:57.030
- [Rachel] Are you ready to go?

42:57.030 --> 42:57.863
- To what?

42:58.830 --> 43:01.017
- [Rachel] To Mark's birthday party.

43:01.017 --> 43:02.430
Greg, you said we were gonna go.

43:02.430 --> 43:03.263
- Okay.

43:03.263 --> 43:04.100
I mean, you said you were gonna go.

43:04.100 --> 43:05.173
I said I was thinking about going.

43:05.173 --> 43:07.240
- [Rachel] Greg, I asked
you about this last week

43:07.240 --> 43:08.580
and you said yes.

43:08.580 --> 43:11.070
- Okay, I don't remember saying that, so.

43:11.070 --> 43:13.070
- [Rachel] God, what
is with you right now?

43:13.070 --> 43:13.903
It's happened three

43:13.903 --> 43:14.963
times this week.
- What's with me right now?

43:14.963 --> 43:16.660
Like, can you not see
what's with me right now?

43:16.660 --> 43:18.990
- [Rachel] Yes, and I can't
depend on you anymore.

43:18.990 --> 43:20.460
- You can't depend on me

43:20.460 --> 43:22.640
to go to a birthday party

43:22.640 --> 43:25.106
to a guy that I barely fucking know.

43:25.106 --> 43:25.939
- You're making commitments

43:25.939 --> 43:27.527
and then you're dropping
them and it makes me

43:27.527 --> 43:28.966
feel like shit.
- That's my commitment.

43:28.966 --> 43:30.510
That's my commitment.

43:30.510 --> 43:31.343
- Okay.

43:31.343 --> 43:32.176
- [Greg] Do you want
me to get an A or not?

43:32.176 --> 43:33.009
That's worth 25%

43:33.009 --> 43:34.595
of my final grade.
- So, what is this?

43:34.595 --> 43:35.428
- [Greg] What?

43:35.428 --> 43:37.170
- Is this not a commitment?

43:37.170 --> 43:38.580
This is your grade, okay, I get it.

43:38.580 --> 43:40.420
But what else, is it really helping you,

43:40.420 --> 43:43.540
this documentary, this
Professor Zardonicus bullshit?

43:43.540 --> 43:45.430
You're chasing a monster. It's not real.

43:45.430 --> 43:46.940
- Before I didn't work hard enough

43:46.940 --> 43:49.330
and now I word too hard.

43:49.330 --> 43:51.080
You can either complain about me--

43:51.080 --> 43:52.370
- Greg, that's work.
- Watching movies and

43:52.370 --> 43:53.750
playing video games all day

43:53.750 --> 43:54.759
or you can complain about me going

43:54.759 --> 43:55.592
not going to parties.
- This isn't work.

43:55.592 --> 43:56.425
What is this?

43:56.425 --> 43:57.422
You're talking about a monster

43:57.422 --> 43:58.903
that doesn't exist, Greg.
- You gotta choose one.

43:59.830 --> 44:02.760
This project exists.

44:02.760 --> 44:04.040
That should be good enough for you.

44:04.040 --> 44:06.090
It's good enough for me.

44:06.090 --> 44:07.893
So just go to the party.

44:09.410 --> 44:10.243
- Great.

44:11.987 --> 44:14.522
All right, it would be great
if you were there but--

44:14.522 --> 44:16.318
- Yeah, whatever.

44:16.318 --> 44:18.493
- [Rachel] All right.

44:18.493 --> 44:20.010
- Tell Mark I said hi.

44:20.010 --> 44:20.843
- [Rachel] Sure.

44:24.603 --> 44:25.436
- Fuck.

44:34.507 --> 44:37.590
(Greg clears throat)

44:40.110 --> 44:42.140
After Darren's video went viral,

44:42.140 --> 44:45.130
he was invited to an interview

44:45.130 --> 44:47.950
at the official university radio station

44:47.950 --> 44:51.250
and the results were to be expected.

44:51.250 --> 44:52.083
- All right, everybody.

44:52.083 --> 44:53.100
Welcome back to the show.

44:53.100 --> 44:54.570
You know what station you're at.

44:54.570 --> 44:56.280
It's your host, Keegan Michaels,

44:56.280 --> 44:58.250
bringing you the latest campus news.

44:58.250 --> 45:01.621
Joining me is a very special guest.

45:01.621 --> 45:03.560
You know that one weird dude

45:03.560 --> 45:05.410
who crashed the poetry slam?

45:05.410 --> 45:09.360
It's our university's
very own Darren Mitchell.

45:09.360 --> 45:11.300
Darren, how are you doing today?

45:11.300 --> 45:12.600
- Well, I'm doing all right, Keegan.

45:12.600 --> 45:13.540
Thank you for asking.

45:13.540 --> 45:14.940
- It's customary.

45:14.940 --> 45:16.810
What I really wanted to know and get to

45:16.810 --> 45:18.830
was more along the lines of

45:18.830 --> 45:21.110
what the hell were you
thinking that night?

45:21.110 --> 45:23.610
- Um, well. (clears throat)

45:23.610 --> 45:26.170
You see, that was a night of expression

45:27.020 --> 45:29.670
and I got up on that
stage to express myself.

45:29.670 --> 45:32.350
- No, everybody else was
expressing themselves.

45:32.350 --> 45:34.480
What you did was you stole the spotlight

45:34.480 --> 45:37.110
away from people who were
sharing their experiences

45:37.110 --> 45:40.570
as members of the LGBT community

45:40.570 --> 45:42.470
to talk some bullshit about a monster.

45:42.470 --> 45:46.570
- Well, okay, Professor
Zardonicus is not a monster.

45:46.570 --> 45:48.440
Hitler was a monster.

45:48.440 --> 45:50.110
Would you compare the victim

45:50.110 --> 45:53.056
of a horrific prank to Adolf Hitler?

45:53.056 --> 45:53.889
(Keegan sighs)

45:53.889 --> 45:54.810
- Okay.

45:54.810 --> 45:57.030
You are a grown ass man.
- I am.

45:57.030 --> 45:58.890
- A student of this university

45:58.890 --> 46:01.950
who would rather choose to spend his time

46:01.950 --> 46:03.840
talking about the Boogie Man.

46:03.840 --> 46:06.700
- Yes, because there are
just so many similarities

46:06.700 --> 46:09.670
between the Boogie Man and
Professor Zardonicus, right?

46:09.670 --> 46:12.890
- Which are figments of
your imagination, so.

46:12.890 --> 46:14.290
- Tell me something, Keegan.

46:15.420 --> 46:18.620
Have you ever met your
great great grandfather?

46:18.620 --> 46:19.880
- Um--
- Let me stop you right there.

46:19.880 --> 46:21.320
You haven't.

46:21.320 --> 46:23.860
Does that make him a
figment of your imagination?

46:23.860 --> 46:25.570
Does that make him not real?

46:25.570 --> 46:27.870
- Darren, the fact that
we have a cameraman

46:27.870 --> 46:30.840
recording this whole thing
clearly makes it obvious

46:30.840 --> 46:32.500
that you're just looking for attention.

46:32.500 --> 46:35.640
- Well, you're the one with
a radio station, Keegan.

46:35.640 --> 46:37.430
Are you just looking for attention?

46:37.430 --> 46:39.530
- No, I'm looking for a story.

46:39.530 --> 46:40.890
- So am I.

46:40.890 --> 46:43.200
Just because my story doesn't align

46:43.200 --> 46:45.050
with societal norms,

46:45.050 --> 46:47.080
doesn't mean that it's not worth telling

46:47.080 --> 46:48.393
or that it's not true.

46:50.488 --> 46:52.810
- Let's go to our student body.

46:52.810 --> 46:54.980
Everyone, I want you to call in

46:54.980 --> 46:57.030
and tell me what you think on the matter.

46:57.960 --> 46:59.680
You're on the air with Keegan.

46:59.680 --> 47:01.010
To whom am I speaking?

47:01.010 --> 47:03.440
- [Casey] Hi, Keegan. My name is Casey.

47:03.440 --> 47:04.770
I'm a junior.

47:04.770 --> 47:06.780
- Nice to be talking to you, Casey.

47:06.780 --> 47:09.590
Tell me, what are your thoughts
about this whole thing?

47:09.590 --> 47:11.560
- [Casey] Well, let's give
the benefit of the doubt

47:11.560 --> 47:15.000
and say this guy really believes
in Professor Zardonicus.

47:15.000 --> 47:17.940
What I have to ask is
how is what you're doing

47:17.940 --> 47:19.680
even getting closer to proving that?

47:19.680 --> 47:22.120
- You don't think I'm
doing a good job, Casey?

47:22.120 --> 47:24.740
- [Casey] I don't even think
you're trying, honestly.

47:24.740 --> 47:26.480
All you do is harass people

47:26.480 --> 47:29.280
and you expect us to
take you on your word?

47:29.280 --> 47:31.140
- How am I harassing people?

47:31.140 --> 47:33.240
I am out there spreading the word

47:33.240 --> 47:35.020
about Professor Zardonicus.

47:35.020 --> 47:37.930
I am making people aware of a creature

47:37.930 --> 47:40.220
that stalks this campus.

47:40.220 --> 47:41.750
If people are aware,

47:41.750 --> 47:43.443
they can find him.

47:44.320 --> 47:46.730
I don't know how else to
explain this to you, Casey.

47:46.730 --> 47:48.170
How am I not coming across?

47:48.170 --> 47:50.170
- [Casey] Honestly, I
think you're just dodging.

47:50.170 --> 47:51.458
I think you're not going after him

47:51.458 --> 47:53.150
because, like the guy said,

47:53.150 --> 47:56.220
you want attention more
than you want this truth.

47:56.220 --> 47:57.490
Why aren't you going out there

47:57.490 --> 47:59.227
and really trying to find this thing?

47:59.227 --> 48:01.440
And why don't you find other witnesses?

48:01.440 --> 48:04.300
There has to be somebody
else who's seen this thing.

48:04.300 --> 48:06.670
Can you say that you have actually gotten

48:06.670 --> 48:08.683
any closer to proving that he's real?

48:11.350 --> 48:13.360
- [Keegan] Got anything to say, Darren?

48:13.360 --> 48:14.995
- I mean, um,

48:14.995 --> 48:19.800
there's just the fact that he's, uh...

48:21.207 --> 48:22.040
(Keegan laughs)

48:22.040 --> 48:23.940
- [Keegan] I think you got him, Casey.

48:27.850 --> 48:29.460
- So, update.

48:29.460 --> 48:31.280
Darren has asked me to come out here

48:31.280 --> 48:34.090
and meet him the middle of the woods.

48:34.090 --> 48:37.400
Which will surely not
end in my violent murder.

