- Yes.

1:01:19.360 --> 1:01:20.193
Yes, I did.

1:01:21.330 --> 1:01:22.858
It was uh...

1:01:22.858 --> 1:01:26.640
It was in the spring semester of '89.

1:01:26.640 --> 1:01:27.756
Yes, I remember.

1:01:27.756 --> 1:01:30.670
I just finished my midterms.

1:01:30.670 --> 1:01:33.280
- But you didn't tell
anyone about the incident?

1:01:33.280 --> 1:01:34.113
- Well, no.

1:01:34.113 --> 1:01:35.550
I didn't tell the newspapers

1:01:35.550 --> 1:01:38.950
because I didn't want
to be a laughing stock.

1:01:38.950 --> 1:01:41.250
And I didn't tell the campus officials

1:01:41.250 --> 1:01:43.260
because, well, I was in a place

1:01:43.260 --> 1:01:44.840
that I wasn't supposed to be.

1:01:44.840 --> 1:01:46.010
- Oh, really?

1:01:46.010 --> 1:01:47.710
Where was this place?

1:01:47.710 --> 1:01:49.763
- The old abandoned science building.

1:01:50.840 --> 1:01:52.390
Yeah.

1:01:52.390 --> 1:01:57.390
It had been shut down and
abandoned for decades.

1:01:57.460 --> 1:01:59.313
But one night we were out there.

1:02:02.037 --> 1:02:03.940
Well, it was all a part of this initiation

1:02:03.940 --> 1:02:06.450
in this fraternity I
was trying to get into.

1:02:06.450 --> 1:02:10.270
They wanted the pledges to spend the night

1:02:10.270 --> 1:02:12.730
in the old abandoned science building.

1:02:12.730 --> 1:02:13.563
And, you know,

1:02:15.040 --> 1:02:16.610
there were rumors that it was haunted

1:02:16.610 --> 1:02:19.650
and people had gone and disappeared and...

1:02:19.650 --> 1:02:22.833
So I was, you know,
thought I was big shit.

1:02:23.720 --> 1:02:27.340
I stumbled in and started
going down the halls

1:02:27.340 --> 1:02:31.873
and then there was just nothing.

1:02:33.560 --> 1:02:36.310
Just all of a sudden there was nothing.

1:02:36.310 --> 1:02:37.420
And um...

1:02:38.810 --> 1:02:41.633
But then I heard the noise.

1:02:44.340 --> 1:02:48.110
You know, I was drunk
off my ass that night

1:02:49.230 --> 1:02:52.423
but I have never ever
heard a sound like that.

1:02:55.580 --> 1:02:58.810
Then I turned around and

1:03:01.350 --> 1:03:05.680
it was on me, this creature.

1:03:05.680 --> 1:03:08.590
And it was coming at me

1:03:08.590 --> 1:03:12.030
and it was, he was swinging his claws,

1:03:12.030 --> 1:03:13.585
these giant claws.

1:03:13.585 --> 1:03:15.752
(sobbing)

1:03:16.857 --> 1:03:18.207
- What else happened, Herb?

1:03:19.878 --> 1:03:21.033
- What happened?

1:03:22.610 --> 1:03:24.480
What happened was I ran.

1:03:24.480 --> 1:03:26.227
I ran and I ran and I ran

1:03:26.227 --> 1:03:27.901
and I ran for my life

1:03:27.901 --> 1:03:32.630
and I just ran until I was
out of the goddamn building

1:03:32.630 --> 1:03:35.113
and I just kept running and running.

1:03:36.270 --> 1:03:38.727
Anyways, the next thing I
know I'm (clears throat),

1:03:41.531 --> 1:03:43.060
well I'm back at my place

1:03:43.060 --> 1:03:45.250
and my friends are all around me

1:03:46.314 --> 1:03:48.023
and they're, you know,

1:03:49.409 --> 1:03:50.840
telling me something happened

1:03:50.840 --> 1:03:52.020
or wondering what happened

1:03:52.020 --> 1:03:54.070
and I don't know what happened and it's--

1:03:55.380 --> 1:03:57.260
- Why didn't you tell anyone, Herb?

1:03:57.260 --> 1:04:00.750
- Well, I wish I had told someone.

1:04:00.750 --> 1:04:03.183
I mean, I wish I had the
guts to tell somebody.

1:04:05.720 --> 1:04:10.030
Listen, you can't do the same, all right.

1:04:10.030 --> 1:04:11.700
If that creature is still out there,

1:04:11.700 --> 1:04:13.440
you can't do the same.

1:04:13.440 --> 1:04:15.970
Do you understand me, son?

1:04:15.970 --> 1:04:18.343
- I understand you completely, Herb.

1:04:21.720 --> 1:04:23.870
Now, not that I'm keeping
track or anything, Greg,

1:04:23.870 --> 1:04:27.320
but I think that's
Darren one, society zero.

1:04:27.320 --> 1:04:28.153
- [Greg] You know, Darren,

1:04:28.153 --> 1:04:29.880
you could've told me what
we were doing out here.

1:04:29.880 --> 1:04:33.260
- I don't know, it didn't
seem relevant at the time.

1:04:33.260 --> 1:04:35.020
- [Greg] It didn't seem relevant?

1:04:35.020 --> 1:04:37.690
Darren, this guy could've been dangerous.

1:04:37.690 --> 1:04:39.850
- Yeah, dangerously woke.

1:04:39.850 --> 1:04:43.010
- [Greg] Darren, that's
such fucking horse shit.

1:04:43.010 --> 1:04:44.000
- What do you mean?

1:04:44.000 --> 1:04:45.360
- [Greg] What do you think
we even did out here?

1:04:45.360 --> 1:04:46.340
What do you think we proved?

1:04:46.340 --> 1:04:48.060
- We just found the tide turner.

1:04:48.060 --> 1:04:51.220
We have another witness
of Professor Zardonicus.

1:04:51.220 --> 1:04:52.053
I'm not alone.

1:04:52.053 --> 1:04:53.330
It proves that I wasn't lying.

1:04:53.330 --> 1:04:55.252
- [Greg] But that can't be--

1:04:55.252 --> 1:04:58.080
- Say, you boys want a drink for the road?

1:04:58.080 --> 1:04:59.230
- Oh, no thanks.

1:04:59.230 --> 1:05:01.040
We're just about to head out.

1:05:01.040 --> 1:05:01.910
You ready, Greg?

1:05:01.910 --> 1:05:03.933
Thank you again, Mr. Kint.

1:05:05.040 --> 1:05:05.873
- Sure.

1:05:07.380 --> 1:05:08.213
No problem.

1:05:09.460 --> 1:05:10.370
- We got a long walk back.

1:05:10.370 --> 1:05:11.700
- [Greg] Let's just go, Darren.

1:05:11.700 --> 1:05:12.533
- All right.
- Fuck.

1:05:12.533 --> 1:05:13.960
- [Darren] I love your place.

1:05:18.300 --> 1:05:21.210
- After today's journey into the woods

1:05:21.210 --> 1:05:23.663
to meet Herbert Kint,

1:05:25.479 --> 1:05:27.723
some developments were made.

1:05:30.230 --> 1:05:35.040
We learned that Darren
might actually be...

1:05:38.028 --> 1:05:39.460
What am I saying?

1:05:39.460 --> 1:05:41.500
We learned that there

1:05:43.774 --> 1:05:46.480
might be more credence...

1:05:53.010 --> 1:05:56.100
So I was thinking about what
Rachel said the other day

1:05:56.100 --> 1:05:56.933
and she's right.

1:05:56.933 --> 1:05:58.600
I don't know anything about Darren.

1:05:58.600 --> 1:05:59.850
I don't know his history.

1:06:01.760 --> 1:06:02.670
Like nothing.

1:06:02.670 --> 1:06:06.733
And with his behavior
becoming even more erratic,

1:06:07.670 --> 1:06:09.220
I thought it would help
to do some research

1:06:09.220 --> 1:06:13.200
and I found out some
pretty interesting things.

1:06:13.200 --> 1:06:17.070
So Darren Mitchell was
born to Ryan Mitchell.

1:06:17.070 --> 1:06:19.170
Ryan Mitchell is an oil and gas guy.

1:06:19.170 --> 1:06:20.003
He's been around forever.

1:06:20.003 --> 1:06:23.840
He's worked with ExxonMobil,
Shell, and Enron.

1:06:23.840 --> 1:06:26.880
Now, there's an unfortunate thing here.

1:06:26.880 --> 1:06:30.000
Darren was not born to
Ryan Mitchell's wife.

1:06:30.000 --> 1:06:33.260
Darren was born to Ryan
Mitchell's secretary.

1:06:33.260 --> 1:06:34.850
So we can probably see where

1:06:34.850 --> 1:06:38.600
some developmental issues start occurring.

1:06:38.600 --> 1:06:40.820
So Darren seemingly
had a normal childhood.

1:06:40.820 --> 1:06:42.140
He was just going to different

1:06:42.140 --> 1:06:44.210
private schools around the country

1:06:44.210 --> 1:06:48.750
until one gap where he just
stopped going to school

1:06:48.750 --> 1:06:49.730
for about two years

1:06:49.730 --> 1:06:52.000
when he was maybe 11 or 12.

1:06:52.000 --> 1:06:55.460
There's no real way to find out why.

1:06:55.460 --> 1:06:57.440
All of this is confidential, of course.

1:06:57.440 --> 1:07:00.330
So, there's only one person I can talk to.

1:07:00.330 --> 1:07:01.900
And if I'm right,

1:07:01.900 --> 1:07:05.703
that person will be getting
out of work right now.

1:07:08.780 --> 1:07:10.463
Hi, Mr. Mitchell?

1:07:11.340 --> 1:07:12.173
Hi, Mr. Mitchell. I need to talk to you.

1:07:12.173 --> 1:07:13.460
- What the hell is this?

1:07:13.460 --> 1:07:15.160
- [Greg] No, I need to talk to you, sir.

1:07:15.160 --> 1:07:16.590
- You can't just accost me like this.

1:07:16.590 --> 1:07:17.780
- [Greg] I'm not accosting you, sir.

1:07:17.780 --> 1:07:19.140
Sir, this is important.

1:07:19.140 --> 1:07:20.253
This is about Darren.

1:07:21.520 --> 1:07:23.370
This is about your son, Mr. Mitchell.

1:07:26.410 --> 1:07:27.243
- Who are you?

1:07:27.243 --> 1:07:30.420
- [Greg] I'm a friend of Darren's and I--

1:07:30.420 --> 1:07:31.253
- Friend?

1:07:31.253 --> 1:07:32.480
- [Greg] Yes.

1:07:32.480 --> 1:07:34.440
And, look, just give me a couple minutes,

1:07:34.440 --> 1:07:37.420
I'll explain, but I do
need to talk to you.

1:07:37.420 --> 1:07:40.640
- You're making a documentary about this?

1:07:40.640 --> 1:07:41.580
- [Greg] Yeah.

1:07:41.580 --> 1:07:43.030
It's for a school assignment.

1:07:44.060 --> 1:07:45.163
- About what again?

1:07:47.170 --> 1:07:48.833
- [Greg] Professor Zardonicus.

1:07:50.380 --> 1:07:52.259
- Ah.
- Yeah, I know.

1:07:52.259 --> 1:07:53.343
- That's a new one.

1:07:54.440 --> 1:07:55.660
- [Greg] I'm sorry. New one?

1:07:55.660 --> 1:07:57.290
What do you mean by that?

1:07:57.290 --> 1:07:58.513
- When my son was a boy,

1:07:59.450 --> 1:08:02.780
he had an overactive imagination.

1:08:02.780 --> 1:08:04.920
Most children are
steadfast in their beliefs

1:08:04.920 --> 1:08:09.920
but Darren was unusually convicted.

1:08:13.540 --> 1:08:16.130
Unfortunately, I indulged his beliefs,

1:08:16.130 --> 1:08:17.483
even the ridiculous ones.

1:08:18.321 --> 1:08:20.571
It was the only thing
that would satisfy him.

1:08:22.330 --> 1:08:23.750
Then I hear from his teachers

1:08:23.750 --> 1:08:27.590
that he has started taking
his stories to school,

1:08:27.590 --> 1:08:30.760
scaring his fellow classmates.

1:08:30.760 --> 1:08:35.210
One year he told us that Santa Claus

1:08:35.210 --> 1:08:36.783
had tried to kidnap him.

1:08:38.040 --> 1:08:39.803
That was a rough Christmas.

1:08:40.990 --> 1:08:43.500
Then I hear that he has started

1:08:43.500 --> 1:08:46.640
luring other children out into the woods.

1:08:46.640 --> 1:08:49.070
I didn't think he would do anything but

1:08:51.610 --> 1:08:54.480
it was time to get him some help.

1:08:54.480 --> 1:08:55.613
So I,

1:08:57.910 --> 1:09:00.900
I sent him to a child psychiatrist

1:09:00.900 --> 1:09:03.030
recommended by my colleagues and...

1:09:06.370 --> 1:09:08.020
- [Greg] And what? What happened?

1:09:11.920 --> 1:09:14.770
- They couldn't find
anything wrong with him.

1:09:14.770 --> 1:09:16.870
Couldn't diagnose him with a single thing.

1:09:21.140 --> 1:09:23.600
I don't know what Darren thinks he saw

1:09:24.980 --> 1:09:26.433
but he wasn't lying.

1:09:27.610 --> 1:09:28.600
Anyway, I...

1:09:30.180 --> 1:09:31.272
I gotta get going.

1:09:31.272 --> 1:09:33.020
I gotta beat the traffic.

1:09:33.020 --> 1:09:35.300
- [Greg] Oh, sure. I understand.

1:09:35.300 --> 1:09:37.430
Look, if you could just not tell Darren

1:09:37.430 --> 1:09:38.580
that we had this conversation,

1:09:38.580 --> 1:09:39.693
I'd appreciate it.

1:09:41.850 --> 1:09:43.700
- You don't have to worry about that.

1:09:46.170 --> 1:09:48.083
My son doesn't speak to me anymore.

1:09:54.030 --> 1:09:55.130
- So that did nothing.

1:09:56.390 --> 1:10:00.290
I learned that Darren has
been to an institution,

1:10:00.290 --> 1:10:02.433
though they couldn't
diagnose him with anything.

1:10:03.280 --> 1:10:04.530
So that doesn't really comfort me

1:10:04.530 --> 1:10:06.140
when he has a long history

1:10:06.140 --> 1:10:08.930
of luring people out into the woods.

1:10:08.930 --> 1:10:11.530
And I don't know how I'm
gonna talk to Darren about it.

1:10:11.530 --> 1:10:13.350
What, am I gonna tell him that I thought

1:10:13.350 --> 1:10:16.170
I ran into his estranged
father at the grocery store

1:10:16.170 --> 1:10:17.710
and we just got to talking

1:10:17.710 --> 1:10:20.530
about his history with delusions?

1:10:20.530 --> 1:10:23.383
I mean, no matter what,
this is a lose lose for me.

1:10:24.400 --> 1:10:25.233
Either Darren's fine

1:10:25.233 --> 1:10:28.870
and I've been just sneaking into his past

1:10:28.870 --> 1:10:30.860
or he's actually unstable

1:10:30.860 --> 1:10:32.780
and I've been exploiting
a mentally ill person

1:10:32.780 --> 1:10:36.923
for a fucking class assignment.

1:10:38.000 --> 1:10:40.500
There is a distinct possibility

1:10:40.500 --> 1:10:43.690
that I don't know what I'm doing

1:10:44.830 --> 1:10:49.830
and that I've really hurt this guy.

1:10:50.630 --> 1:10:52.420
'Cause this, this right here,

1:10:52.420 --> 1:10:54.343
cannot be healthy for him.

1:10:54.343 --> 1:10:56.080
I've just created an atmosphere

1:10:56.080 --> 1:10:57.040
where I make him think

1:10:57.040 --> 1:10:58.543
that this behavior is okay.

1:11:00.800 --> 1:11:04.503
I've indulged him and for what?

1:11:05.430 --> 1:11:07.260
I don't know if I should
tell him that he needs help,

1:11:07.260 --> 1:11:09.940
but I can't keep indulging this, right?

1:11:09.940 --> 1:11:11.850
I can't keep pretending that thing...

1:11:13.680 --> 1:11:14.513
What the fuck?

1:11:16.450 --> 1:11:17.283
Shit.

1:11:22.670 --> 1:11:23.503
Darren?

1:11:23.503 --> 1:11:25.030
- Hello, Gregory.

1:11:25.030 --> 1:11:27.052
- [Greg] What are you doing here?

1:11:27.052 --> 1:11:29.902
- I have some very important
information to relay to you.

1:11:30.940 --> 1:11:32.350
- [Greg] Okay.

1:11:32.350 --> 1:11:33.860
This couldn't have been over the phone?

1:11:33.860 --> 1:11:35.240
- I'm sure it could've been over the phone

1:11:35.240 --> 1:11:37.050
if you want the NSA to eavesdrop on us

1:11:37.050 --> 1:11:39.700
and have us murdered and
covered up as a suicide, yeah.

1:11:39.700 --> 1:11:41.480
But I don't think that's
what either of us wants.

1:11:41.480 --> 1:11:43.390
So the more important question is

1:11:43.390 --> 1:11:46.003
thank you for saving my life, Darren.

1:11:46.003 --> 1:11:47.250
- [Greg] That's not even a question.

1:11:47.250 --> 1:11:48.780
- Keep the camera up here.

1:11:48.780 --> 1:11:49.930
- [Greg] Can we keep this short?

1:11:49.930 --> 1:11:54.090
- I mean, as short as
uncovering and verbally sharing

1:11:54.090 --> 1:11:55.460
a piece of crucial information

1:11:55.460 --> 1:11:56.570
to our investigation can be.

1:11:56.570 --> 1:11:57.790
Sure, I'll keep it short.

1:11:57.790 --> 1:12:02.160
- [Greg] Okay, and this is
not technically my apartment.

1:12:02.160 --> 1:12:04.490
So if you could just
be careful around shit.

1:12:04.490 --> 1:12:06.780
- You have a key, right?

1:12:06.780 --> 1:12:09.493
- What?
- You have a key?

1:12:09.493 --> 1:12:10.326
You have a key

1:12:10.326 --> 1:12:11.159
to the apartment?
- My girlfriend gave me a key

1:12:11.159 --> 1:12:12.330
but this--
- Perfect. Then let me in.

1:12:12.330 --> 1:12:13.500
I've been waiting.

1:12:13.500 --> 1:12:14.333
Is she not here?

1:12:14.333 --> 1:12:15.280
- Fuck.
- Keep the camera up here.

1:12:15.280 --> 1:12:16.630
- Okay, goddammit.

1:12:16.630 --> 1:12:17.630
Darren, what are you doing here?

1:12:17.630 --> 1:12:19.860
- How much does this thing cost exactly?

1:12:19.860 --> 1:12:21.260
- [Greg] The coffee maker? I don't know.

1:12:21.260 --> 1:12:23.240
- Yeah, I mean, the only reason I asked

1:12:23.240 --> 1:12:24.820
is because I have one just like it

1:12:24.820 --> 1:12:26.440
and I think it's starting
to break down on me

1:12:26.440 --> 1:12:28.600
'cause this morning I made
myself a cup of coffee

1:12:28.600 --> 1:12:30.350
and it was just, it was mostly grain.

1:12:30.350 --> 1:12:32.400
There was hardly any liquid in it at all.

1:12:32.400 --> 1:12:33.640
And it's hard to start the morning

1:12:33.640 --> 1:12:34.687
with a mouthful of grain,
you know what I mean?

1:12:34.687 --> 1:12:37.840
- [Greg] Did you come to
talk about coffee grains?

1:12:37.840 --> 1:12:39.420
Why are you here, Darren?

1:12:39.420 --> 1:12:40.810
Just tell me why you're here.

1:12:40.810 --> 1:12:43.200
- No reason, nothing big except...

1:12:43.200 --> 1:12:44.310
Oh, oh yeah, I remember now.

1:12:44.310 --> 1:12:46.560
I know where to find Professor Zardonicus.

1:12:48.040 --> 1:12:49.190
- [Greg] What?

1:12:49.190 --> 1:12:50.570
- Don't tell me you already forgot

1:12:50.570 --> 1:12:51.803
who Professor Zardonicus is, Greg.

1:12:51.803 --> 1:12:53.140
- [Greg] I didn't forget who he was.

1:12:53.140 --> 1:12:54.548
I just...

1:12:54.548 --> 1:12:55.381
Okay.

1:12:56.290 --> 1:12:58.050
How? Was, where?

1:12:58.050 --> 1:12:59.590
- I don't know how I can explain it

1:12:59.590 --> 1:13:00.850
any simpler than that, Greg.

1:13:00.850 --> 1:13:02.670
I know where he is, where he lives,

1:13:02.670 --> 1:13:04.630
the place he rests his head at night,

1:13:04.630 --> 1:13:06.440
where he keeps all of
his magazines, you know.

1:13:06.440 --> 1:13:07.690
The place--
- Hey, Greg?

1:13:08.885 --> 1:13:10.821
Are we still going to the movie?

1:13:10.821 --> 1:13:11.654
It's about to start.
- How long have you

1:13:11.654 --> 1:13:13.993
been standing there?

1:13:13.993 --> 1:13:15.080
- A second.

1:13:15.080 --> 1:13:17.320
- Greg, did you see her walk in?

1:13:17.320 --> 1:13:18.740
- [Greg] Yeah, I mean, she lives here

1:13:18.740 --> 1:13:19.850
so I didn't think it was a big deal.

1:13:19.850 --> 1:13:22.040
- This is a private conversation, Greg.

1:13:22.040 --> 1:13:24.020
Two ears only. No third parties.

1:13:24.020 --> 1:13:25.483
- I can just go.

1:13:27.330 --> 1:13:28.190
- No.

1:13:28.190 --> 1:13:29.720
No, she already fucking ruined it.

1:13:29.720 --> 1:13:31.727
The whole ambience is just...

1:13:32.888 --> 1:13:34.110
- Greg, what's going on?
- I don't know.

1:13:34.110 --> 1:13:35.195
I don't...

1:13:35.195 --> 1:13:36.833
We're just having like
a production meeting.

1:13:36.833 --> 1:13:38.330
- I would be much more comfortable

1:13:38.330 --> 1:13:39.380
if we talked in here.

1:13:40.400 --> 1:13:41.480
- [Greg] The closet?

1:13:41.480 --> 1:13:42.420
- Yeah.
- The fucking closet?

1:13:42.420 --> 1:13:43.253
- The closet.

1:13:43.253 --> 1:13:44.210
I would be much more comfortable

1:13:44.210 --> 1:13:45.500
if we had this conversation in here

1:13:45.500 --> 1:13:47.300
and I assume my comfort matters to you.

1:13:47.300 --> 1:13:48.870
- Like I said, I can just go.

1:13:48.870 --> 1:13:50.860
- Oh, I'm so glad you can do something.

1:13:50.860 --> 1:13:52.370
I didn't hear you the first time.

1:13:52.370 --> 1:13:56.450
Greg, will you say something?
- Hey!

1:13:56.450 --> 1:13:58.540
I'm not going in the closet.

1:13:58.540 --> 1:14:00.540
I'm not.
- If you're not

1:14:00.540 --> 1:14:01.423
going in the closet,

1:14:01.423 --> 1:14:03.290
then I'm gonna stop speaking entirely.

1:14:03.290 --> 1:14:04.890
- Greg, don't go into the closet.

1:14:04.890 --> 1:14:06.033
- [Greg] I'm not going in the closet.

1:14:06.033 --> 1:14:08.030
- Then I'm gonna stop
speaking starting now.

1:14:08.030 --> 1:14:10.258
- Oh, so if I said that
Professor Zardonicus

1:14:10.258 --> 1:14:11.580
is a little horseshit--

1:14:11.580 --> 1:14:12.413
- I would!

1:14:12.413 --> 1:14:14.770
I would say you're full of shit.

1:14:14.770 --> 1:14:17.470
But I'm not speaking, so there's that.

1:14:17.470 --> 1:14:19.220
- [Greg] We can go anywhere else, okay?

1:14:19.220 --> 1:14:20.550
We can go to a cafe.

1:14:20.550 --> 1:14:21.580
We can go to a library.

1:14:21.580 --> 1:14:23.540
Just not the fucking closet.

1:14:23.540 --> 1:14:26.110
- If I was speaking I would
say that's a great idea.

1:14:26.110 --> 1:14:26.943
But I'm not speaking, so there's that.

1:14:26.943 --> 1:14:28.940
- Greg, you're not actually
humoring this, are you?

1:14:28.940 --> 1:14:32.320
- There's nothing humorous about this.

1:14:32.320 --> 1:14:34.823
Now, Greg, go in the closet with me.

1:14:35.980 --> 1:14:36.830
- [Greg] I can't go in the closet.

1:14:36.830 --> 1:14:37.668
- Please, Greg.

1:14:37.668 --> 1:14:38.868
You and me in the closet together now.

1:14:38.868 --> 1:14:40.050
- Fucking stop it!

1:14:40.050 --> 1:14:41.718
- You'd better not follow
us in there either!

1:14:41.718 --> 1:14:42.960
- I don't plan on following

1:14:42.960 --> 1:14:44.032
you into the closet.
- I see it in your eyes.

1:14:44.032 --> 1:14:44.865
- What's even going on here?
You're gonna follow

1:14:44.865 --> 1:14:45.710
us in there.

1:14:45.710 --> 1:14:46.840
Are you gonna stand out here with a cup

1:14:46.840 --> 1:14:47.741
to the door and listen?
- I am not going into

1:14:47.741 --> 1:14:48.574
the closet with you.

1:14:48.574 --> 1:14:49.407
What are you doing?
- Is that what you want?

1:14:49.407 --> 1:14:51.269
(all shouting)

1:14:51.269 --> 1:14:52.240
This whole fucking time!

1:14:52.240 --> 1:14:53.790
- [Greg] Jesus fucking Christ, Darren.

1:14:53.790 --> 1:14:57.030
I mean you have been an idiot for most--

1:14:57.030 --> 1:14:58.750
- The science building.

1:14:58.750 --> 1:14:59.583
- [Greg] What?

1:14:59.583 --> 1:15:00.416
- The old science building.

1:15:00.416 --> 1:15:01.249
That's where we find him.

1:15:01.249 --> 1:15:02.460
There's where Herb ran into him.

1:15:02.460 --> 1:15:03.540
That's where he was created,

1:15:03.540 --> 1:15:05.580
where Professor Zardonicus was born.

1:15:05.580 --> 1:15:07.750
It's been right in front of
our face this entire time.

1:15:07.750 --> 1:15:08.920
We're going down there tonight

1:15:08.920 --> 1:15:10.833
and we're proving to the
world once and for all

1:15:10.833 --> 1:15:13.158
that Professor Zardonicus is real.

1:15:13.158 --> 1:15:13.991
(soft guitar music)

1:15:13.991 --> 1:15:15.290
- [Greg] Okay, you are asking me

1:15:15.290 --> 1:15:18.723
to do something very very stupid, Darren.

1:15:19.900 --> 1:15:21.300
If we go there, if we're caught--

1:15:21.300 --> 1:15:24.090
- If he's not there, I'll quit.

1:15:24.090 --> 1:15:25.350
There's nowhere else to look, Greg.

1:15:25.350 --> 1:15:26.360
This is it.

1:15:26.360 --> 1:15:27.970
Our last chance.

1:15:27.970 --> 1:15:29.320
- [Greg] Do you actually mean that?

1:15:29.320 --> 1:15:31.350
- [Darren] I wouldn't say
it if I didn't mean it.

1:15:31.350 --> 1:15:33.190
- [Greg] If he's not
down there, we're done.

1:15:33.190 --> 1:15:34.360
Completely done.

1:15:34.360 --> 1:15:35.193
- That's what I'm saying.

1:15:35.193 --> 1:15:36.260
- [Greg] I have your word on that?

1:15:36.260 --> 1:15:37.093
- Yes.

1:15:39.290 --> 1:15:40.123
- [Greg] Okay.

1:15:45.470 --> 1:15:47.730
Hey, look, I got something I gotta do.

1:15:47.730 --> 1:15:48.830
Just give me a minute.

1:15:49.920 --> 1:15:50.760
Uh, hey.

1:15:50.760 --> 1:15:53.440
So, I know that was weird
and that I've been weird

1:15:53.440 --> 1:15:57.570
but I can promise you that
tonight is the last night.

1:15:57.570 --> 1:15:58.620
- [Rachel] Where are you going?

1:15:58.620 --> 1:15:59.670
- [Greg] It doesn't matter.

1:15:59.670 --> 1:16:01.220
He said he's gonna quit.

1:16:01.220 --> 1:16:02.640
That means we can put
everything behind us.

1:16:02.640 --> 1:16:04.170
It means you never have to hear

1:16:04.170 --> 1:16:06.233
the name Professor Zardonicus ever again.

1:16:07.196 --> 1:16:08.840
- [Rachel] Okay.

1:16:08.840 --> 1:16:09.673
- Okay?
- Yeah.

1:16:11.540 --> 1:16:12.483
- [Greg] Thank you.

1:16:13.330 --> 1:16:14.413
I will be back.

1:16:15.890 --> 1:16:17.550
Soon, I hope.

1:16:17.550 --> 1:16:19.360
Okay, love you. Bye.

1:16:19.360 --> 1:16:22.990
- Today is November 5th, 2019.

1:16:22.990 --> 1:16:24.590
I, Darren James Mitchell,

1:16:24.590 --> 1:16:26.990
am standing in front of
the old science building

1:16:26.990 --> 1:16:29.150
which also serves as the resting place

1:16:29.150 --> 1:16:30.573
for Professor Zardonicus.

1:16:31.680 --> 1:16:34.050
As we reach the end of my journey,

1:16:34.050 --> 1:16:35.370
I look back on all the times

1:16:35.370 --> 1:16:38.703
my partner and I were met
with mockery and scorn.

1:16:40.290 --> 1:16:41.680
I think back on my life

1:16:42.780 --> 1:16:44.390
and how at times it seemed like

1:16:44.390 --> 1:16:45.883
nothing more than a sad joke.

1:16:47.800 --> 1:16:51.120
In many ways I have much more
in common with the Professor

1:16:51.120 --> 1:16:53.710
than I do with, say, regular people.

1:16:53.710 --> 1:16:58.620
He was the subject of a
horrific and cruel prank

1:16:58.620 --> 1:17:00.470
which transformed him into something,

1:17:01.390 --> 1:17:03.663
something less than he was before.

1:17:04.640 --> 1:17:08.693
I do not wish to harm the
Professor or judge him in any way.

1:17:09.830 --> 1:17:11.280
My allegiance is to the truth

1:17:12.288 --> 1:17:13.588
and the truth I shall have

1:17:14.525 --> 1:17:15.833
at all costs.

1:17:17.208 --> 1:17:18.430
(loud clattering)

1:17:18.430 --> 1:17:19.592
- What?
- Did you hear that?

1:17:19.592 --> 1:17:20.920
- [Greg] What?

1:17:20.920 --> 1:17:22.572
- Come on.
- What?

1:17:22.572 --> 1:17:23.553
The fuck are we going?

1:17:23.553 --> 1:17:24.845
Where are we...

1:17:24.845 --> 1:17:26.020
Darren!

1:17:26.020 --> 1:17:26.853
Darren, slow down, slow down.
- Shit.

1:17:26.853 --> 1:17:29.520
Holy fuck. Where are we?
- He's in here somewhere.

1:17:29.520 --> 1:17:32.113
- [Greg] Okay, let's just
make this quick, all right?

1:17:32.113 --> 1:17:32.946
- There it is.

1:17:32.946 --> 1:17:34.723
I thought I forgot it.
- What the fuck?

1:17:34.723 --> 1:17:35.733
- [Darren] What?

1:17:35.733 --> 1:17:37.870
- [Greg] Is that a gun? A real gun?

1:17:37.870 --> 1:17:39.530
- No, Greg, I brought a fake gun

1:17:39.530 --> 1:17:41.270
to fight a very real monster.

1:17:41.270 --> 1:17:42.870
What do you think?

1:17:42.870 --> 1:17:44.270
- [Greg] I think you're gonna go to jail

1:17:44.270 --> 1:17:45.103
when somebody finds you with that.

1:17:45.103 --> 1:17:47.580
- Oh, I'm sorry I wanted to
be at least a little prepared

1:17:47.580 --> 1:17:49.410
if we're hunting down a monster.

1:17:49.410 --> 1:17:51.320
- [Greg] You can't keep doing
this shit to me, Darren.

1:17:51.320 --> 1:17:52.153
- Doing what?

1:17:53.313 --> 1:17:55.930
- [Greg] All the fucking mystery stuff

1:17:55.930 --> 1:17:57.600
where you put me through a heart attack.

1:17:57.600 --> 1:17:58.820
I thought we were partners!

1:17:58.820 --> 1:18:00.770
- We are partners, Greg.

1:18:00.770 --> 1:18:02.373
- [Greg] Then why don't you
console me about anything?

1:18:02.373 --> 1:18:04.760
- Because I don't wanna
make things more complicated

1:18:04.760 --> 1:18:05.593
than they have to be.

1:18:05.593 --> 1:18:07.050
- [Greg] Oh, like they're
not complicated right now?

1:18:07.050 --> 1:18:08.580
Doesn't this feel complicated?

1:18:08.580 --> 1:18:10.300
- Because I don't wanna
get into a little fight

1:18:10.300 --> 1:18:12.030
over every single thing, all right?

1:18:12.030 --> 1:18:13.080
This is not a big deal.

1:18:13.080 --> 1:18:14.830
Everything's worked out so far.

1:18:14.830 --> 1:18:16.407
- [Greg] Says the man
with lipstick on his face.

1:18:16.407 --> 1:18:18.404
- That's not the point.

1:18:18.404 --> 1:18:19.735
- [Greg] Okay, Darren, stop.

1:18:19.735 --> 1:18:21.083
We need to talk.

1:18:22.160 --> 1:18:23.493
Darren, I said stop.

1:18:24.790 --> 1:18:25.623
Fuck.

1:18:25.623 --> 1:18:27.463
Darren, stop or I turn off the camera!

1:18:29.190 --> 1:18:30.420
- What?

1:18:30.420 --> 1:18:31.600
- [Greg] Yeah.

1:18:31.600 --> 1:18:33.050
Well, that did it, didn't it?

1:18:34.350 --> 1:18:35.183
That's all this is,

1:18:35.183 --> 1:18:37.540
is just showing off
for the fucking camera.

1:18:37.540 --> 1:18:39.270
- What are you saying, Greg?

1:18:39.270 --> 1:18:43.220
- [Greg] I'm saying that the only reason

1:18:43.220 --> 1:18:45.530
you pretend to need me,

1:18:45.530 --> 1:18:47.620
like when you obviously have enough money

1:18:47.620 --> 1:18:48.930
to buy your own equipment,

1:18:48.930 --> 1:18:50.370
to buy whatever you need,

1:18:50.370 --> 1:18:54.660
it's just to satisfy your own ego.

1:18:54.660 --> 1:18:55.783
- I never said that.

1:18:56.830 --> 1:18:58.180
- [Greg] You don't have to.

1:18:59.410 --> 1:19:01.520
You need the one thing
that money can't buy you

1:19:01.520 --> 1:19:03.000
and that's the validation.

1:19:03.000 --> 1:19:04.390
- You're making stuff up now.

1:19:04.390 --> 1:19:06.300
- [Greg] Am I? Am I really?

1:19:06.300 --> 1:19:09.107
Dude, okay, that is the
only reason we're down here.

1:19:09.107 --> 1:19:10.140
That's the only reason

1:19:10.140 --> 1:19:12.550
I'm walking around a
fucking basement with you

1:19:12.550 --> 1:19:15.203
looking for something
that doesn't even exist!

1:19:17.040 --> 1:19:18.080
- Wait, you don't...

1:19:19.178 --> 1:19:20.629
You don't believe in Professor Zardonicus?

1:19:20.629 --> 1:19:22.223
- [Greg] Of course I don't!

1:19:23.680 --> 1:19:24.650
Jesus Christ.

1:19:24.650 --> 1:19:26.300
- [Darren] So you've been
lying to me this whole time.

1:19:26.300 --> 1:19:28.100
- [Greg] Okay, don't
turn this on me, dude.

1:19:28.100 --> 1:19:30.390
- No, what about that night
at the fountain, Greg?

1:19:30.390 --> 1:19:31.223
- What?
- Did you see

1:19:31.223 --> 1:19:32.140
Professor Zardonicus then

1:19:32.140 --> 1:19:35.227
or were you just lying for
some sort of sick joke?

1:19:35.227 --> 1:19:36.610
- Do not--
- Is that all this whole

1:19:36.610 --> 1:19:37.888
experience has been?
- Do not pretend

1:19:37.888 --> 1:19:40.280
that you don't have some serous issues.

1:19:40.280 --> 1:19:42.840
- Oh, I'm sorry that
I'm able to comprehend

1:19:42.840 --> 1:19:45.280
something beyond your
limited scope of imagination.

1:19:45.280 --> 1:19:47.070
- [Greg] And I'm sorry that
you're fucking delusional

1:19:47.070 --> 1:19:48.570
just like when you were a kid.

1:19:50.057 --> 1:19:50.950
(Greg sighs)

1:19:50.950 --> 1:19:52.030
Okay, I'm sorry.

1:19:52.030 --> 1:19:52.910
- What'd you just say?

1:19:52.910 --> 1:19:53.743
- [Greg] I shouldn't have said that.

1:19:53.743 --> 1:19:55.750
I'm sorry.
- When I was a kid?

1:19:55.750 --> 1:19:57.490
- Yes, I, look--
- Have you been snooping

1:19:57.490 --> 1:19:58.590
around my past, Greg?
- No, I've been

1:19:58.590 --> 1:19:59.423
doing research.

1:19:59.423 --> 1:20:00.890
I've been doing research.

1:20:00.890 --> 1:20:02.353
I'm making a documentary.
- You talk about trust.

1:20:02.353 --> 1:20:04.068
- I had to do research.
- You talk about understanding

1:20:04.068 --> 1:20:06.017
having each other's back?
- Hey, hey! Put the gun down!

1:20:06.017 --> 1:20:06.850
Put the fucking gun down.
- Then you pull

1:20:06.850 --> 1:20:08.082
this shit, Greg.

1:20:08.082 --> 1:20:09.520
- [Greg] Put the gun down, Darren.

1:20:09.520 --> 1:20:10.353
- I'm not gonna put the gun down

1:20:10.353 --> 1:20:12.060
because you're a fucking liar

1:20:12.060 --> 1:20:13.430
and you're going behind my back.

1:20:13.430 --> 1:20:14.266
- [Greg] You're not
gonna put the gun down?

1:20:14.266 --> 1:20:15.734
- You're supposed to be my partner, Greg!

1:20:15.734 --> 1:20:17.600
- Okay, fuck you.
- What?

1:20:17.600 --> 1:20:18.710
- I'm out.
- No.

1:20:18.710 --> 1:20:19.906
- I'm really out, man.
- You're not being...

1:20:19.906 --> 1:20:20.750
- [Greg] You crossed the fucking line.

1:20:20.750 --> 1:20:21.870
- Stop it! Greg!
- No, no!

1:20:21.870 --> 1:20:26.107
Let go of the fucking
camera, you son of a...

1:20:26.107 --> 1:20:26.953
Ah, fuck.

1:20:27.823 --> 1:20:29.530
Are you okay?
- Get away from me.

1:20:29.530 --> 1:20:30.834
- What?
- Get away from me, Greg.

1:20:30.834 --> 1:20:31.667
- [Greg] What happened? What?

1:20:31.667 --> 1:20:32.850
Did you get hurt?
- Just go away!

1:20:32.850 --> 1:20:35.806
- Wait, wait, wait.
- Please.

1:20:35.806 --> 1:20:36.910
Stop, Greg.

1:20:36.910 --> 1:20:38.610
- [Greg] Where are the scars?

1:20:38.610 --> 1:20:39.983
- Please, Greg, stop.

1:20:40.960 --> 1:20:42.627
- [Greg] Where are the scars, Darren?

1:20:42.627 --> 1:20:44.130
(Darren sobbing)

1:20:44.130 --> 1:20:45.173
Show them to me.

1:20:52.760 --> 1:20:53.669
It was all a lie?

1:20:53.669 --> 1:20:55.233
- No.

1:20:55.233 --> 1:20:57.078
- [Greg] You're just a fucking liar.

1:20:57.078 --> 1:20:58.443
- No, it wasn't a lie.
- You're such a fucking liar.

1:20:58.443 --> 1:21:01.730
- Please, Greg, I just
needed someone to believe me.

1:21:01.730 --> 1:21:04.530
- [Greg] All of your
pretentious bullshit about truth

1:21:04.530 --> 1:21:05.363
and you're just a fucking liar!

1:21:05.363 --> 1:21:07.963
- I just needed you to
believe in me, please.

1:21:08.883 --> 1:21:10.732
I didn't know what else to do.

1:21:10.732 --> 1:21:13.687
I'm sorry, I didn't
mean to hurt you, Greg.

1:21:13.687 --> 1:21:15.010
Where are you going?
- Truth my fucking ass.

1:21:15.010 --> 1:21:16.690
- Where are you going?
- I'm leaving, Darren.

1:21:16.690 --> 1:21:19.180
What does it look like?
- Please don't leave me.

1:21:19.180 --> 1:21:20.240
You can't leave me down here with him.

1:21:20.240 --> 1:21:22.183
He'll kill me.

1:21:22.183 --> 1:21:23.940
Please, Greg.
- Yeah?

1:21:23.940 --> 1:21:26.200
- Please.
- Good luck.

1:21:26.200 --> 1:21:27.750
- Greg.
- Bye, Darren.

1:21:27.750 --> 1:21:28.583
- [Darren] Greg, no.

1:21:28.583 --> 1:21:30.228
No, Greg, please!

1:21:30.228 --> 1:21:32.811
(Greg panting)

1:21:41.020 --> 1:21:45.564
- This is Greg Hartman of comm 43...

1:21:45.564 --> 1:21:47.113
I can't remember the name.

1:21:49.577 --> 1:21:50.950
I have to announce that

1:21:52.080 --> 1:21:54.710
the Zardonicus project, my final project,

1:21:54.710 --> 1:21:58.090
is officially canceled.

1:21:58.090 --> 1:21:59.450
I just can't...

1:22:01.590 --> 1:22:03.280
I just can't...

1:22:04.260 --> 1:22:05.280
I'm sorry, Professor,

1:22:05.280 --> 1:22:06.653
and I hope you understand.

1:22:07.868 --> 1:22:10.375
(creature roaring)
(Greg screams)

1:22:10.375 --> 1:22:11.605
What the fuck?

1:22:11.605 --> 1:22:12.438
What the?

1:22:18.850 --> 1:22:20.935
(tense music)

1:22:20.935 --> 1:22:23.024
- Oh God, please.
- Darren?

1:22:23.024 --> 1:22:25.590
- [Darren] Please, go away.

1:22:25.590 --> 1:22:26.998
- [Greg] Darren, that's you, right?

1:22:26.998 --> 1:22:29.070
- Please, Greg, help me.

1:22:29.070 --> 1:22:31.737
Help me, Greg, help me!
- Darren!

1:22:34.798 --> 1:22:35.812
- Greg, are you still there?
- Darren?

1:22:35.812 --> 1:22:37.945
- Help me, Greg, please.

1:22:37.945 --> 1:22:39.412
- Darren!

1:22:39.412 --> 1:22:40.795
Don't kill him!

1:22:40.795 --> 1:22:43.878
(tense guitar music)

1:23:00.689 --> 1:23:02.142
(creature roars)

1:23:02.142 --> 1:23:04.017
Darren! What the.

1:23:04.017 --> 1:23:04.850
Darren?

1:23:06.580 --> 1:23:08.364
What the fuck.

1:23:08.364 --> 1:23:12.550
(creature roars)
(Greg screams)

1:23:12.550 --> 1:23:13.383
Darren?

1:23:15.190 --> 1:23:16.023
Oh.

1:23:16.938 --> 1:23:19.250
Oh.

1:23:19.250 --> 1:23:20.083
Darren.

1:23:21.610 --> 1:23:23.720
You don't have to do this, Darren.

1:23:23.720 --> 1:23:24.670
You really don't.

1:23:24.670 --> 1:23:25.830
I believe you now.

1:23:25.830 --> 1:23:26.813
No, I believe you.

1:23:26.813 --> 1:23:29.170
Darren, I believe you.

1:23:29.170 --> 1:23:31.299
I believe you, Darren.

