It hasn't been too long

1:25:19.580 --> 1:25:22.413
since I was on the other
end of this operation.

1:25:23.309 --> 1:25:25.150
- Okay, well, first of all,

1:25:25.150 --> 1:25:28.150
I just wanna say thank you for doing this.

1:25:28.150 --> 1:25:28.983
- Oh yeah, sure.

1:25:28.983 --> 1:25:31.723
- I know it's been a lot for you.

1:25:33.680 --> 1:25:34.700
- It is what it is, right?

1:25:34.700 --> 1:25:36.130
- Mm-hmm.

1:25:36.130 --> 1:25:38.880
So, I just wanna start off,

1:25:38.880 --> 1:25:43.100
just how are you now after everything?

1:25:43.100 --> 1:25:43.933
- Sure.

1:25:46.570 --> 1:25:50.710
Well, since Darren's disappearance,

1:25:50.710 --> 1:25:53.343
things have changed for me a lot.

1:25:55.150 --> 1:25:56.460
So, I'm sure you guys know this,

1:25:56.460 --> 1:25:58.490
but after everything came out

1:25:58.490 --> 1:26:01.230
about what Darren and I were up to,

1:26:01.230 --> 1:26:03.980
a huge scandal came out of it

1:26:03.980 --> 1:26:07.430
and the film department decided

1:26:07.430 --> 1:26:09.403
to put me under academic probation.

1:26:10.240 --> 1:26:11.190
And on top of that,

1:26:12.270 --> 1:26:15.160
the footage that I had
been shooting leaked

1:26:16.244 --> 1:26:17.740
and everybody saw it

1:26:19.090 --> 1:26:20.600
and all these intimate moments

1:26:20.600 --> 1:26:21.903
that Darren and I had.

1:26:22.960 --> 1:26:27.960
Seeing those from a
stranger's eyes, I guess,

1:26:28.840 --> 1:26:32.340
puts a different perspective
on the whole thing

1:26:33.205 --> 1:26:35.873
and I just couldn't be on that campus

1:26:35.873 --> 1:26:38.023
without thinking about him, honestly.

1:26:39.480 --> 1:26:41.396
I decided to cut the cord.

1:26:41.396 --> 1:26:42.229
Fuck.

1:26:42.229 --> 1:26:44.653
I decided to cut the cord
and drop out of school.

1:26:47.230 --> 1:26:51.483
Which sounds like a pretty
dumb idea right now.

1:26:54.470 --> 1:26:56.400
My girlfriend at the time was a very,

1:26:56.400 --> 1:26:58.310
she still is, a very ambitious person

1:26:58.310 --> 1:27:01.380
and I think we both realized

1:27:01.380 --> 1:27:02.980
that I was just dead weight to her

1:27:02.980 --> 1:27:06.783
and that I probably had
been for a very long time.

1:27:07.670 --> 1:27:10.337
And yeah, that was the end of that.

1:27:10.337 --> 1:27:12.763
So I'm kinda on my own these days.

1:27:14.070 --> 1:27:14.903
- Okay.

1:27:16.570 --> 1:27:17.573
I'm sorry.

1:27:21.540 --> 1:27:23.460
I kinda wanna focus more on Darren now,

1:27:23.460 --> 1:27:24.463
if you don't mind.

1:27:24.463 --> 1:27:25.563
I just wanna know,

1:27:27.450 --> 1:27:30.260
'cause I know you've been looking for him.

1:27:30.260 --> 1:27:32.420
- Well, I mean, looking for him,

1:27:32.420 --> 1:27:33.830
I don't expect to find him.

1:27:33.830 --> 1:27:37.040
What I've done is I've
created a movement of sorts

1:27:37.040 --> 1:27:40.227
to try to reach out to him, you know.

1:27:40.227 --> 1:27:42.713
I want him to come back to me.

1:27:43.580 --> 1:27:45.250
I want it to be a mutual thing

1:27:46.658 --> 1:27:49.200
'cause I don't blame him for feeling

1:27:49.200 --> 1:27:51.140
that I took advantage of him

1:27:51.140 --> 1:27:52.960
and that I exploited him.

1:27:52.960 --> 1:27:56.480
So I want him to know
that I do care about him

1:27:56.480 --> 1:27:58.620
and that I am sorry

1:27:58.620 --> 1:28:02.580
and I've just been putting up
these flyers and everything

1:28:02.580 --> 1:28:06.490
hoping to hear back from him.

1:28:06.490 --> 1:28:08.980
Obviously, nothing's come from that but

1:28:10.500 --> 1:28:11.870
it does feel good knowing

1:28:11.870 --> 1:28:14.170
that I am doing what I'm
supposed to be doing.

1:28:16.060 --> 1:28:17.520
That's not something I've ever

1:28:17.520 --> 1:28:20.640
really been able to say
before but I can say it now

1:28:20.640 --> 1:28:24.050
and that's at least one positive thing

1:28:25.960 --> 1:28:28.100
I can say about this whole mess.

1:28:28.100 --> 1:28:29.510
- Okay.

1:28:29.510 --> 1:28:31.090
Does this involve anything

1:28:31.090 --> 1:28:34.420
with Professor Zardonicus by any means?

1:28:34.420 --> 1:28:39.050
I mean, you did say that
you believe you saw him.

1:28:39.050 --> 1:28:40.003
- Well, okay.

1:28:41.260 --> 1:28:42.750
This is gonna be a little complicated

1:28:42.750 --> 1:28:43.823
so just bear with me.

1:28:45.160 --> 1:28:49.920
I saw him and I saw
Darren Mitchell that night

1:28:49.920 --> 1:28:51.473
together.
- You saw, okay.

1:28:52.490 --> 1:28:54.520
Both of them in the basement, right?

1:28:54.520 --> 1:28:55.353
In the old science building.

1:28:55.353 --> 1:28:58.120
- I saw them both at the same time.

1:28:58.120 --> 1:29:00.750
- So you believe that Zardonicus took him?

1:29:00.750 --> 1:29:01.583
- No.

1:29:03.470 --> 1:29:04.450
- I'm sorry, I'm just,

1:29:04.450 --> 1:29:05.283
I'm having a hard time following.

1:29:05.283 --> 1:29:08.270
- No, I'm not good at explaining this.

1:29:08.270 --> 1:29:11.133
You know these guys.

1:29:13.115 --> 1:29:15.705
Professor Zardonicus is a good example.

1:29:15.705 --> 1:29:18.100
- Like Big Foot?
- Big Foot, Loch Ness Monster.

1:29:18.100 --> 1:29:18.933
- Okay.

1:29:18.933 --> 1:29:20.814
- We have all of these guys

1:29:20.814 --> 1:29:23.720
and they're not creatures
and monsters to us.

1:29:23.720 --> 1:29:25.600
That's not why we care.

1:29:25.600 --> 1:29:28.523
It's that they're Rorschach tests, really.

1:29:29.690 --> 1:29:32.780
It's that they are what
we need them to be.

1:29:32.780 --> 1:29:34.843
And Professor Zardonicus,

1:29:37.760 --> 1:29:39.670
Darren needed him to be real.

1:29:39.670 --> 1:29:41.280
He needed that.

1:29:41.280 --> 1:29:44.762
And so what he did was he made him real.

1:29:44.762 --> 1:29:46.610
- I mean, to me it just sounds like

1:29:46.610 --> 1:29:50.350
you think that Darren had
just dressed up as a monster.

1:29:50.350 --> 1:29:52.590
- I mean, I'm dressed up right now.

1:29:52.590 --> 1:29:54.440
You guys all here, you're dressed up.

1:29:55.750 --> 1:29:58.313
Right? Like--
- Yes.

1:29:59.670 --> 1:30:01.710
- It's all about appearances

1:30:01.710 --> 1:30:03.710
and it's all about becoming

1:30:03.710 --> 1:30:05.383
that thing you were meant to be.

1:30:07.132 --> 1:30:07.965
I mean,

1:30:09.550 --> 1:30:12.650
what I saw that night, it
was Professor Zardonicus.

1:30:12.650 --> 1:30:14.130
You may not wanna call him that,

1:30:14.130 --> 1:30:16.720
but that's what he was to me.

1:30:16.720 --> 1:30:18.340
- So you're essentially saying

1:30:18.340 --> 1:30:21.393
that Darren became Professor Zardonicus?

1:30:22.300 --> 1:30:26.580
- I'm saying that Darren realized

1:30:26.580 --> 1:30:29.063
to make something real
you have to believe.

1:30:30.370 --> 1:30:34.283
But to get people to
believe, it has to be real.

1:30:35.170 --> 1:30:37.350
- I do not wish to harm the Professor

1:30:37.350 --> 1:30:39.313
or judge him in any way.

1:30:40.220 --> 1:30:41.890
But my allegiance is to the truth

1:30:42.760 --> 1:30:44.060
and the truth I shall have

1:30:45.037 --> 1:30:46.663
at all costs.

1:30:51.290 --> 1:30:52.700
Was that good or...

1:30:53.657 --> 1:30:57.530
I mean, I felt like it
was pretty good overall.

1:30:57.530 --> 1:30:59.443
I don't think it was too rehearsed.

1:31:01.347 --> 1:31:02.240
Yeah.

1:31:02.240 --> 1:31:03.386
All right.

